<A>__{with a camera bag slung over her shoulder, anne marie climbs up the metal antenna tower behind neff's house on the edge of town. she grits her teeth and fights back a wave of vertigo. the ground disappears from sight, hidden by the snow and fog. fifty feet up, she attaches her infrared video camera to the tower crossbars and, using a length of coaxial cable, hooks its rf output to the feedline of the community tv antenna.}
